graph.io

Class JGraphConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • graph.io.JGraphConverter

  • public class JGraphConverter
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains the methods for generating an associated JGraph object for a DMGraph object, for display purposes.

      • dmGraphToJGraph

        public static org.jgraph.JGraph dmGraphToJGraph(DMGraph g,
                                double[][] coordinates,
                                double[] scale,
                                int featureType,
                                int featureIndex)
                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Converts a DMGraph object to a JGraph object. This method assumes that the scale and coordinates are given separately, though in fact they can also be given within the VertexInstances in the graph.
        Parameters:
        g - DMGraph to be converted.
        coordinates - double[][] representing the vertex coordinates.
        scale - double[] representing vertex scales.
        featureType - Integer representing the feature type for display.
        featureIndex - Integer representing the feature index to display.
        Returns:
        JGraph that corresponds to the provided DMGraph.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
